Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.86,0:00:05.44,English1,,0,0,0,,We live on one level of existence, but there are others.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.46,0:00:10.14,English1,,0,0,0,,These hidden dimensions of reality are everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:12.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Far away, across the light years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:13.94,English1,,0,0,0,,Beneath our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.94,0:00:17.24,English1,,0,0,0,,And even inside you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.58,0:00:20.04,English1,,0,0,0,,We are made of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:23.74,English1,,0,0,0,,There are more atoms in your eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:27.28,English1,,0,0,0,,than there are stars and all the galaxies\Nof the known universe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.04,0:00:34.18,English1,,0,0,0,,The same is true of any solid object
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.21,0:00:36.91,English1,,0,0,0,,larger than the tip of your little finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:40.78,English1,,0,0,0,,I'm a collection of three billion, billion, billion
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:43.72,English1,,0,0,0,,intricately arranged atoms called Neil Degrasse Tyson.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:48.59,English1,,0,0,0,,You are a similar collection with a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.63,0:00:50.13,English1,,0,0,0,,We don't usually think of ourselves this way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.16,0:00:54.20,English1,,0,0,0,,because that level of reality lies beyond the realm of our senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:00:56.43,English1,,0,0,0,,But we're not gonna let that stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.47,0:00:59.64,English1,,0,0,0,,We can go deeper into the wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Atoms let matter do funny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:49.73,English1,,0,0,0,,To understand water, you need to know what its atoms are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.76,0:02:52.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Every molecule of water is composed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:53.83,English1,,0,0,0,,of two tiny hydrogen atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.87,0:02:56.50,English1,,0,0,0,,attached to a larger oxygen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.54,0:02:58.61,English1,,0,0,0,,That's why we call it H20.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.64,0:03:01.74,English1,,0,0,0,,If it's not too hot or too cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.44,English1,,0,0,0,,the molecules can slide and tumble past each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.48,0:03:06.75,English1,,0,0,0,,There's still some stickiness between the molecules,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.78,0:03:10.02,English1,,0,0,0,,but not enough to lock them into a rigid solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.05,0:03:12.79,English1,,0,0,0,,That's what makes something a liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.82,0:03:14.45,English1,,0,0,0,,The sun warms the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.49,0:03:15.86,English1,,0,0,0,,And with more energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.89,0:03:17.79,English1,,0,0,0,,the molecules move faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.83,0:03:19.59,English1,,0,0,0,,That's all that temperature is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.63,0:03:21.59,English1,,0,0,0,,Those molecules are moving fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:24.76,English1,,0,0,0,,to break the weak bonds that hold them to their neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:26.67,English1,,0,0,0,,That's evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.70,0:03:28.60,English1,,0,0,0,,The air we breathe is made of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:30.64,English1,,0,0,0,,nitrogen and oxygen molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:34.44,English1,,0,0,0,,with a scattering of water vapor and carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.47,0:03:36.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Incoming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:38.71,English1,,0,0,0,,That's condensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.75,0:03:41.31,English1,,0,0,0,,A dewdrop is the momentary triumph
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.35,0:03:43.45,English1,,0,0,0,,of condensation over evaporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.48,0:03:45.22,English1,,0,0,0,,And while it lasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.25,0:03:48.69,English1,,0,0,0,,it's a little cosmos with its own worlds...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:51.99,English1,,0,0,0,,creatures, drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:55.43,English1,,0,0,0,,To explore the far-flung realms of this dewdrop
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:56.89,English1,,0,0,0,,we're gonna need a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:00.13,English1,,0,0,0,,One with twin engines...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.53,English1,,0,0,0,,science and imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.51,0:04:10.41,English1,,0,0,0,,That's a single-celled paramecium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:13.21,English1,,0,0,0,,one of a multitude of skilled hunter-warriors
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:15.85,English1,,0,0,0,,that roam the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.88,0:04:18.42,English1,,0,0,0,,But they, too, are hunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:23.02,English1,,0,0,0,,The Dileptus. The paramecium's mortal enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:26.82,English1,,0,0,0,,The paramecium might get lucky and score a direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:28.53,English1,,0,0,0,,Even if it doesn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:31.09,English1,,0,0,0,,the recoil from the barrage will put some distance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:32.96,English1,,0,0,0,,between the paramecium and its attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:38.00,English1,,0,0,0,,What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.03,0:04:39.80,English1,,0,0,0,,That's life in the dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.88,0:04:54.38,English1,,0,0,0,,That little guy is tardigrade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:57.82,English1,,0,0,0,,an animal smaller than the head of a pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.22,0:05:02.22,English1,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:04.23,English1,,0,0,0,,Tardigrades have been living on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:05.53,English1,,0,0,0,,a lot longer than we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.56,0:05:08.33,English1,,0,0,0,,About 500 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.80,0:05:12.80,English1,,0,0,0,,For every one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.84,0:05:16.00,English1,,0,0,0,,there's at least a billion of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.07,0:05:21.38,English1,,0,0,0,,They can make a living anywhere on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.41,0:05:25.05,English1,,0,0,0,,In the frigid peaks of the tallest mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.92,English1,,0,0,0,,in the cauldrons of erupting volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.95,0:05:29.45,English1,,0,0,0,,and in the deep ocean vents at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:30.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Tardigrades are so tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.92,0:05:32.22,English1,,0,0,0,,they can survive naked
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:34.32,English1,,0,0,0,,in the vacuum of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.36,0:05:36.66,English1,,0,0,0,,They've survived all five
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:38.99,English1,,0,0,0,,of the most recent mass extinctions on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.03,0:05:42.30,English1,,0,0,0,,A visitor from another world could be forgiven
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.33,0:05:45.70,English1,,0,0,0,,for thinking of earth as the planet of the tardigrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.47,0:05:53.47,English1,,0,0,0,,If we're ever gonna get to the bottom of this dewdrop\Nbetter get a move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.94,0:05:59.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Every leaf and tiny clump of moss
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.08,English1,,0,0,0,,has hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.12,0:06:03.58,English1,,0,0,0,,of microscopic mouths called Stomata.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.62,0:06:05.59,English1,,0,0,0,,Plants breathe through them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:07.09,English1,,0,0,0,,taking in carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:09.96,English1,,0,0,0,,and exhaling the oxygen that we need to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:12.29,English1,,0,0,0,,The plants can survive without us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.33,0:06:14.53,English1,,0,0,0,,But we and all the other animals...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:17.70,English1,,0,0,0,,we'd be toast without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.93,English1,,0,0,0,,The plants make food out of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.97,0:06:22.33,English1,,0,0,0,,We animals can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:24.30,English1,,0,0,0,,To see how they do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.34,0:06:25.84,English1,,0,0,0,,we have to go deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:27.94,English1,,0,0,0,,make ourselves about a thousand times smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.97,0:06:30.71,English1,,0,0,0,,to get into their treasure house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:32.48,English1,,0,0,0,,the place where they keep the good stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.51,0:06:34.38,English1,,0,0,0,,the chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:35.85,English1,,0,0,0,,That's the molecule
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.88,0:06:38.98,English1,,0,0,0,,that converts sunlight into energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.89,0:06:44.06,English1,,0,0,0,,Every one of those rectangles is a plant cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:46.06,English1,,0,0,0,,And those tiny green vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:48.96,English1,,0,0,0,,are its energy factories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:50.56,English1,,0,0,0,,If we could steal their trade secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:53.13,English1,,0,0,0,,it would trigger a new industrial revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.17,0:06:54.97,English1,,0,0,0,,But to spy on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:56.93,English1,,0,0,0,,we're gonna need to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:11.05,English1,,0,0,0,,What alien world has the ship of the imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.09,0:07:13.32,English1,,0,0,0,,carried us to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:15.56,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:19.23,English1,,0,0,0,,Contained within a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:22.20,English1,,0,0,0,,We're on an industrial espionage mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.23,0:07:24.67,English1,,0,0,0,,If we can penetrate the trade secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.70,0:07:27.57,English1,,0,0,0,,of the manufacturing process in that chloroplast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:30.41,English1,,0,0,0,,let's just say our whole future hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.44,0:07:33.68,English1,,0,0,0,,This chloroplast is using sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.71,0:07:35.38,English1,,0,0,0,,to break water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:37.88,English1,,0,0,0,,into atoms of hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:40.18,English1,,0,0,0,,It combines the hydrogen with carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.22,0:07:41.88,English1,,0,0,0,,to make sugar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:45.22,English1,,0,0,0,,and releases the oxygen as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:48.09,English1,,0,0,0,,To see how it happens, we have to go even deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:49.72,English1,,0,0,0,,get even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.76,0:07:52.99,English1,,0,0,0,,We're talking atomic scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:54.66,English1,,0,0,0,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:56.60,English1,,0,0,0,,This assembly line is the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:07:58.33,English1,,0,0,0,,of the molecular industrial complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:00.33,English1,,0,0,0,,At the molecular level,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:02.37,English1,,0,0,0,,things happen too fast for us to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:04.77,English1,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to slow them down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.81,0:08:07.04,English1,,0,0,0,,about a billion times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:11.95,English1,,0,0,0,,Those larger molecules are carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.98,0:08:13.45,English1,,0,0,0,,Each one of them is made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.48,0:08:15.35,English1,,0,0,0,,of one carbon and two oxygen atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.38,0:08:18.55,English1,,0,0,0,,When sunlight strikes a green molecule of chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:21.72,English1,,0,0,0,,it sets in motion a series of chemical reactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:23.56,English1,,0,0,0,,breaking apart water molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.59,0:08:26.39,English1,,0,0,0,,and freeing energetic electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.63,0:08:30.26,English1,,0,0,0,,And that's just the day shift,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:33.13,English1,,0,0,0,,when sunlight supplies the incoming stream of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.17,0:08:36.10,English1,,0,0,0,,There's a second shift that works day and night
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.14,0:08:38.97,English1,,0,0,0,,using the solar energy kept in reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:43.21,English1,,0,0,0,,The energy of the free electrons is put to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:47.41,English1,,0,0,0,,combining carbon dioxide with hydrogen from the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:52.12,English1,,0,0,0,,The end product is sugar,which stores the solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.15,0:08:55.09,English1,,0,0,0,,The chloroplast is a three-billion-year-old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:57.62,English1,,0,0,0,,solar energy collector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.66,0:09:00.39,English1,,0,0,0,,This sub-microscopic solar battery
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:02.93,English1,,0,0,0,,is what drives all the forests and the fields
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:05.16,English1,,0,0,0,,and the plankton of the seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:06.90,English1,,0,0,0,,And the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.93,0:09:08.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.30,English1,,0,0,0,,The solar-powered biosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.34,0:09:16.84,English1,,0,0,0,,collects and processes six times more power\Nthan our entire civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.88,0:09:18.78,English1,,0,0,0,,We understand on a chemical level
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.81,0:09:20.48,English1,,0,0,0,,how photosynthesis works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:22.61,English1,,0,0,0,,We can recreate the process in a laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:25.42,English1,,0,0,0,,But we're not as good at it as plants are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.45,0:09:27.48,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's not surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:29.92,English1,,0,0,0,,considering nature has been at this for billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.95,0:09:32.02,English1,,0,0,0,,and we've only just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.06,0:09:33.59,English1,,0,0,0,,But if we could figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.62,0:09:35.86,English1,,0,0,0,,the trade secrets of photosynthesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.89,0:09:39.73,English1,,0,0,0,,every of other source of energy we depend on today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:42.43,English1,,0,0,0,,coal, oil, natural gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.87,English1,,0,0,0,,would become obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.90,0:09:47.54,English1,,0,0,0,,Photosynthesis is the ultimate green power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:49.44,English1,,0,0,0,,It doesn't pollute the air
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:51.84,English1,,0,0,0,,and is, in fact, carbon neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:54.81,English1,,0,0,0,,Artificial photosynthesis on a big enough scale
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:56.85,English1,,0,0,0,,could reduce the greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.88,0:10:00.02,English1,,0,0,0,,that's driving climate change in a dangerous direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:02.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, place is evaporating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.59,0:10:04.02,English1,,0,0,0,,Time to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.66,0:10:09.12,English1,,0,0,0,,How fleeting is the life of a dewdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.16,0:10:12.33,English1,,0,0,0,,It condenses from thin air in the cool of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:14.50,English1,,0,0,0,,only to vanish with the heat of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.53,0:10:17.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And what of its inhabitants, the tardigrades?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:19.13,English1,,0,0,0,,They'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:21.57,English1,,0,0,0,,They can go without water for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.67,0:10:24.54,English1,,0,0,0,,It's hard to imagine,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.57,0:10:26.21,English1,,0,0,0,,but plants covered the surface of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:29.01,English1,,0,0,0,,for hundreds of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:32.48,English1,,0,0,0,,before they put forth their first flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.51,0:10:35.38,English1,,0,0,0,,That was about a hundred million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:38.05,English1,,0,0,0,,shortly before the dinosaurs were wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:42.22,English1,,0,0,0,,Our world must've been a relatively\Ndrab-looking place back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:45.49,English1,,0,0,0,,dominated by shades of green and brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:49.83,English1,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there were giant trees and ferns and other plant life,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.86,0:10:52.10,English1,,0,0,0,,but not the purple of an iris
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:55.27,English1,,0,0,0,,or the crimson of a red, red rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:04.68,English1,,0,0,0,,Orchids were among the first flowering species
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:08.58,English1,,0,0,0,,to appear on earth, and they're the most diverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.32,0:11:13.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Darwin was particularly fascinated
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.59,0:11:15.42,English1,,0,0,0,,by the comet orchid of Madagascar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.46,0:11:19.03,English1,,0,0,0,,a flower whose pollen is hidden at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.06,0:11:23.40,English1,,0,0,0,,of a very long, thin spur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:26.27,English1,,0,0,0,,There can be no stronger test of an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:28.30,English1,,0,0,0,,than its predictive power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.04,English1,,0,0,0,,On the basis of his theory of evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.07,0:11:31.47,English1,,0,0,0,,through natural selection
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:34.14,English1,,0,0,0,,Darwin speculated that somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.17,0:11:37.94,English1,,0,0,0,,on the island of Madagascar, there must live flying insects
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:41.08,English1,,0,0,0,,with extraordinarily lengthy tongues,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:42.95,English1,,0,0,0,,ones long enough to reach the pollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:46.55,English1,,0,0,0,,No one had ever seen such a beast there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:48.29,English1,,0,0,0,,but Darwin insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.32,0:11:51.62,English1,,0,0,0,,that an animal fitting this description must exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.39,English1,,0,0,0,,Few people at the time believed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.43,0:11:56.93,English1,,0,0,0,,It wasn't until more than 50 years later
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:11:59.26,English1,,0,0,0,,that Darwin was proven right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:04.84,English1,,0,0,0,,In 1903, a huge hawk moth, called the Morgan's sphinx
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.87,0:12:06.47,English1,,0,0,0,,was discovered in Madagascar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:10.01,English1,,0,0,0,,Attracted by the Comet Orchid's scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:14.35,English1,,0,0,0,,the moth slurps its pollen with its foot-long tongue,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:16.85,English1,,0,0,0,,exactly as Darwin expected it would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:24.82,English1,,0,0,0,,It's even more amazing that the\NMorgan's sphinx was discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.86,0:12:27.26,English1,,0,0,0,,when you consider that more than 90%
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.29,0:12:30.69,English1,,0,0,0,,of Madagascar's rain forest had been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:33.46,English1,,0,0,0,,In the years since Darwin's famous prediction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.50,0:12:36.67,English1,,0,0,0,,this moth species could have easily become extinct
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:39.47,English1,,0,0,0,,with all the others...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.50,0:12:42.71,English1,,0,0,0,,every one of them a unique phrase of life's poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:46.74,English1,,0,0,0,,written in the atoms by eons of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:54.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Ah, the fragrance of lilacs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.32,English1,,0,0,0,,It's one of those scents
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.35,0:12:59.39,English1,,0,0,0,,that triggers a whole constellation of associations,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:02.52,English1,,0,0,0,,all those junes of long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.33,English1,,0,0,0,,But how does that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.36,0:13:07.73,English1,,0,0,0,,How does a smell prompt a movie to\Nstart running in your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:09.73,English1,,0,0,0,,It's not something we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.77,0:13:12.03,English1,,0,0,0,,Could it be a wave of energy, like light?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:15.50,English1,,0,0,0,,Or is it some kind of microscopic particle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:17.21,English1,,0,0,0,,It's actually a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.24,0:13:21.01,English1,,0,0,0,,Every odor we can sense, whether it comes from burnt toast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.04,0:13:24.51,English1,,0,0,0,,gasoline, or a field of lilacs,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:26.75,English1,,0,0,0,,is a cloud of molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.59,English1,,0,0,0,,These molecules have particular shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:32.55,English1,,0,0,0,,When I inhale them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:36.56,English1,,0,0,0,,they stimulate a particular set\Nof receptor cells in my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:40.79,English1,,0,0,0,,An electrical signal then travels to my brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.80,0:13:43.46,English1,,0,0,0,,which identifies the scent as lilac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:48.90,English1,,0,0,0,,Other scents are carried by different molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.90,0:13:51.57,English1,,0,0,0,,with different shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.57,0:13:54.88,English1,,0,0,0,,But when I smell a flower or the smoke from a campfire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:13:56.61,English1,,0,0,0,,or the grease from a motor gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.71,English1,,0,0,0,,I'm often flooded with memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:04.18,English1,,0,0,0,,Why is it that a simple thing such as the scent of a flower
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:07.05,English1,,0,0,0,,can trigger powerful memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.09,0:14:13.59,English1,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the way our brains have evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.59,0:14:15.96,English1,,0,0,0,,Our sense of smell kicks in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:18.56,English1,,0,0,0,,when the olfactory nerve in our brain is stimulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.33,0:14:23.70,English1,,0,0,0,,That nerve is located very close to the amygdala,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:28.64,English1,,0,0,0,,a structure that is integral to our experience of emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.64,0:14:31.91,English1,,0,0,0,,It's also very close to the Hippocampus,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:33.68,English1,,0,0,0,,which helps us form memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:39.85,English1,,0,0,0,,The network of neurons that carry the scent signal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:42.69,English1,,0,0,0,,from my nose to my brain has been fine-tuned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.69,0:14:45.76,English1,,0,0,0,,over hundreds of millions of years of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.86,0:14:50.16,English1,,0,0,0,,It's a survival mechanism that can alert us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:53.03,English1,,0,0,0,,to danger or guide us to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:57.63,English1,,0,0,0,,If you you can detect the predator
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:15:00.67,English1,,0,0,0,,before he's near enough to strike,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:03.01,English1,,0,0,0,,or the fire before it traps you in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.01,0:15:05.18,English1,,0,0,0,,you have a much better chance to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:08.01,English1,,0,0,0,,and pass on your genes to the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.79,0:15:16.35,English1,,0,0,0,,That lovely scent from this field of flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:19.39,English1,,0,0,0,,sets off a unique combination of nerve signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:22.99,English1,,0,0,0,,Only that exact combination can crack the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.99,0:15:26.73,English1,,0,0,0,,where the memory of lilacs is stored inside my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:33.00,English1,,0,0,0,,Wonder who they're for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:36.54,English1,,0,0,0,,Maybe we'll find out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.54,0:15:40.48,English1,,0,0,0,,But first, there's another hidden cosmos waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:03.11,English1,,0,0,0,,The plants are softly breathing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:06.01,English1,,0,0,0,,inhaling molecules of carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:08.74,English1,,0,0,0,,and exhaling molecules of oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:10.25,English1,,0,0,0,,And I'm doing the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:13.62,English1,,0,0,0,,Unlike snowflakes and fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:15.42,English1,,0,0,0,,atoms or molecules of the same kind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:18.55,English1,,0,0,0,,are utterly identical to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:20.26,English1,,0,0,0,,With every breath we take,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:23.46,English1,,0,0,0,,we inhale as many molecules as there are stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:26.03,English1,,0,0,0,,in all the galaxies in the visible universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.06,0:16:29.10,English1,,0,0,0,,And every breath we exhale is circulated through the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:31.63,English1,,0,0,0,,and mixed gradually across the continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.67,0:16:35.60,English1,,0,0,0,,it becomes available for others to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:36.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Breathe with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:51.29,English1,,0,0,0,,We all just inhaled about 100 million molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.32,0:16:53.49,English1,,0,0,0,,that once passed through the lungs of everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.52,0:16:55.56,English1,,0,0,0,,who ever lived before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.59,0:16:58.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Think of it... This kind of atomic reincarnation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.79,0:17:01.06,English1,,0,0,0,,is another link to our distant ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:04.60,English1,,0,0,0,,including those who first launched us on our explorations
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.63,0:17:06.77,English1,,0,0,0,,of the unseen universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.80,0:17:10.24,English1,,0,0,0,,These universes are as real as you or me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.27,0:17:12.47,English1,,0,0,0,,and they surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:19.35,English1,,0,0,0,,There was a moment when we awakened
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.38,0:17:21.98,English1,,0,0,0,,to a new way of thinking and seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:25.45,English1,,0,0,0,,It happened about 2,500 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.49,0:17:27.29,English1,,0,0,0,,on the Greek islands that lie
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.32,0:17:30.59,English1,,0,0,0,,between the empires of the east and west.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.62,0:17:34.69,English1,,0,0,0,,There, merchants, tourists and sailors freely mingled,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.73,0:17:37.83,English1,,0,0,0,,exchanging tales of great kings and gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:42.33,English1,,0,0,0,,In Ionian cities and towns like Miletus, in what is now Turkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:44.54,English1,,0,0,0,,the most fundamental elements
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.57,0:17:47.47,English1,,0,0,0,,of the way we live now first appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.91,0:17:55.18,English1,,0,0,0,,Here, for the first time,\Nreenactments of aspects of life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.21,0:17:58.15,English1,,0,0,0,,created and executed by professionals
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:18:00.99,English1,,0,0,0,,with the expectation of touching something deep
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.02,0:18:02.79,English1,,0,0,0,,within the hearts of the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:05.69,English1,,0,0,0,,or just making them laugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.72,0:18:10.19,English1,,0,0,0,,The first plays, dramas and comedies, were performed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.39,0:18:12.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Here, also, was born a radical new idea:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:15.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Government by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:19.47,English1,,0,0,0,,The first inklings, imperfect then as now, of a democracy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:23.77,English1,,0,0,0,,and the notion that the ordinary citizen\Nmight possess certain rights
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.84,0:18:27.41,English1,,0,0,0,,come to us from this time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:31.65,English1,,0,0,0,,But in my view, the most revolutionary innovation of all
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.68,0:18:35.49,English1,,0,0,0,,to come to us from this ancient world was the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:41.46,English1,,0,0,0,,that natural events were neither punishment nor reward\Nfrom capricious gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:44.73,English1,,0,0,0,,The workings of nature could be explained
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:47.90,English1,,0,0,0,,without invoking the supernatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:50.20,English1,,0,0,0,,The first person to express this thought
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:52.44,English1,,0,0,0,,was a man named Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.47,0:18:54.44,English1,,0,0,0,,When the thunder clapped or the earth quaked,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.47,0:18:59.64,English1,,0,0,0,,it was not because something you did had somehow displeased\Nthe very demanding gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.71,0:19:02.81,English1,,0,0,0,,No, it was the result of natural processes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:05.05,English1,,0,0,0,,that we were capable of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:08.78,English1,,0,0,0,,Though none of the books he is\Nsaid to have written survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:12.85,English1,,0,0,0,,Thales kindled a flame that still burns to this day:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:14.92,English1,,0,0,0,,The very idea of cosmos out of chaos,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:20.73,English1,,0,0,0,,a universe governed by the order of natural laws\Nthat we can actually figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.36,0:19:25.87,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the epic adventure that\Nbegan in the mind of Thales.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:30.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Only a century following Thales' death,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.47,0:19:32.04,English1,,0,0,0,,another genius came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.07,0:19:34.38,English1,,0,0,0,,And he, more than any other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.41,0:19:36.61,English1,,0,0,0,,was the first to discover the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.64,0:19:39.65,English1,,0,0,0,,of the hidden universes that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:43.75,English1,,0,0,0,,Democritus of Abdera was a true scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:47.15,English1,,0,0,0,,a man with a passionate desire to know the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.19,0:19:48.96,English1,,0,0,0,,and to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.99,0:19:52.29,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the man who once said, "a life without parties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.33,0:19:55.73,English1,,0,0,0,,would be like an endless road without an end."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:57.50,English1,,0,0,0,,You mean, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:19:59.13,English1,,0,0,0,,That's all there is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:01.73,English1,,0,0,0,,Just a bunch of atoms in a void?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.77,0:20:02.74,English1,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.44,0:20:05.77,English1,,0,0,0,,Well, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.81,0:20:07.57,English1,,0,0,0,,The world has to be made
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:10.91,English1,,0,0,0,,of countless indivisible particles in a void.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.94,0:20:15.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, nothing could move or grow,\Nbe divided or changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:20.35,English1,,0,0,0,,Without atoms and empty space for them to move in,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.45,0:20:23.65,English1,,0,0,0,,the world would be solid, static, and dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.00,0:20:26.40,English1,,0,0,0,,so don't be sad, my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.44,0:20:28.91,English1,,0,0,0,,Just think of the infinite possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.94,0:20:32.71,English1,,0,0,0,,that arise from different arrangements of those atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.65,0:20:38.18,English1,,0,0,0,,Here's to the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.22,0:20:42.25,English1,,0,0,0,,in this cup and in this wine...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:44.76,English1,,0,0,0,,And to the laughter they make possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.79,0:20:49.83,English1,,0,0,0,,Dispersed through the Clay of the cup
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.86,0:20:51.99,English1,,0,0,0,,are microscopic mineral grains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:54.66,English1,,0,0,0,,different kinds of crystals,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:58.27,English1,,0,0,0,,each with its own distinctive atomic architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.30,0:21:00.77,English1,,0,0,0,,Mineral structures are exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:03.77,English1,,0,0,0,,but they have a limited repertoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.81,0:21:07.04,English1,,0,0,0,,A grain of quartz is a lattice of the same three atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.08,0:21:10.91,English1,,0,0,0,,repeated, without variation, over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:16.49,English1,,0,0,0,,Even a relatively complex mineral lattice like topaz,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:18.95,English1,,0,0,0,,composed of ten or so atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.99,0:21:21.62,English1,,0,0,0,,can only repeat the identical atomic structure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.66,0:21:23.66,English1,,0,0,0,,again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.92,0:21:29.96,English1,,0,0,0,,To leave the matter to another dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.99,0:21:33.36,English1,,0,0,0,,to free it from the lattice prison of endless repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.40,0:21:37.43,English1,,0,0,0,,you need an atom that can bond in all directions\Nwith other atoms like itself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.50,0:21:40.40,English1,,0,0,0,,as well as with atoms of different kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.84,0:21:50.34,English1,,0,0,0,,Behold the carbon atom...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:53.55,English1,,0,0,0,,the essential element for life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:56.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.45,0:22:01.15,English1,,0,0,0,,Carbon is special because it can bond with\Nup to four other atoms at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.19,0:22:03.92,English1,,0,0,0,,It can connect with many different kinds of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.96,0:22:06.93,English1,,0,0,0,,as well as other carbon atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:08.59,English1,,0,0,0,,It can curl into rings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:10.83,English1,,0,0,0,,and string together into chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.86,0:22:15.27,English1,,0,0,0,,building molecules far more\Ncomplex than any crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.47,0:22:21.37,English1,,0,0,0,,No other atom has the same flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.41,0:22:23.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Even atoms that have similar chemical properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.88,0:22:25.44,English1,,0,0,0,,like silicon,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.48,0:22:29.68,English1,,0,0,0,,can't form the amazing variety of molecules built on carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.65,0:22:32.18,English1,,0,0,0,,The carbon-based molecules we call proteins,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:34.39,English1,,0,0,0,,the molecules of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.42,0:22:37.59,English1,,0,0,0,,contain literally hundreds of thousands of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:43.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Carbon atoms are the backbone of the molecules\Nthat make every living thing on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.83,0:22:46.30,English1,,0,0,0,,including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.33,0:22:49.57,English1,,0,0,0,,That's the difference between rocks and living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:53.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Life can make enormous molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.67,0:22:56.14,English1,,0,0,0,,of stunning size and complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.18,0:22:58.28,English1,,0,0,0,,freeing matter to improvise,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.31,0:23:00.31,English1,,0,0,0,,evolve,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.34,0:23:02.35,English1,,0,0,0,,and even love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.30,0:23:35.34,English1,,0,0,0,,Take it easy, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.37,0:23:37.78,English1,,0,0,0,,He never actually touched her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:39.91,English1,,0,0,0,,In everyday life on our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:41.55,English1,,0,0,0,,on the scale of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.58,0:23:45.45,English1,,0,0,0,,material objects never really touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.48,0:23:48.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Each atom has a tiny nucleus at its center,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.92,0:23:52.29,English1,,0,0,0,,surrounded by an electron cloud\Nof lines of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.32,0:23:54.79,English1,,0,0,0,,As the atoms approach each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.83,0:23:56.76,English1,,0,0,0,,the boy's electron clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.79,0:23:58.36,English1,,0,0,0,,push away the girl's.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.40,0:24:02.53,English1,,0,0,0,,More than 99.9% of the matter of any atom
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:04.73,English1,,0,0,0,,is concentrated in its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.77,0:24:08.21,English1,,0,0,0,,The nucleus is surrounded by an electron cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:10.61,English1,,0,0,0,,which produces an invisible field of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.64,0:24:12.91,English1,,0,0,0,,and acts like a shock absorber.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.95,0:24:15.58,English1,,0,0,0,,The configuration of the electron cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.62,0:24:17.58,English1,,0,0,0,,determines the nature of an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.62,0:24:20.25,English1,,0,0,0,,In the ordinary course of things here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.29,0:24:22.15,English1,,0,0,0,,the nuclei never touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.19,0:24:24.26,English1,,0,0,0,,We have a sensation of touching,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.29,0:24:26.89,English1,,0,0,0,,but that's really just our invisible force fields
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.93,0:24:29.86,English1,,0,0,0,,overlapping and repelling each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.64,0:24:48.08,English1,,0,0,0,,The nucleus is very small
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.11,0:24:49.75,English1,,0,0,0,,compared to the rest of the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.78,0:24:53.78,English1,,0,0,0,,If an atom were the size of this cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.82,0:24:58.06,English1,,0,0,0,,its nucleus would be the size of that mote of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.83,0:25:05.03,English1,,0,0,0,,An atom is mostly empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.06,0:25:07.77,English1,,0,0,0,,To understand the nature of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.80,0:25:09.77,English1,,0,0,0,,we have to go deeper still,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.80,0:25:12.80,English1,,0,0,0,,to a place 100,000 times smaller than the atom:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.84,0:25:14.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Its nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.01,0:25:22.38,English1,,0,0,0,,The simplest and most plentiful atom\Nin the cosmos is hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.48,0:25:24.68,English1,,0,0,0,,Its nucleus is a single proton,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.72,0:25:27.72,English1,,0,0,0,,which makes hydrogen element number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:29.55,English1,,0,0,0,,The clouds that surround it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.59,0:25:34.46,English1,,0,0,0,,are the realms where the atom's lone electron\Nis permitted to roam.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.56,0:25:37.79,English1,,0,0,0,,What happens when you have a nucleus with two protons?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.83,0:25:39.46,English1,,0,0,0,,Protons repel each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.50,0:25:41.83,English1,,0,0,0,,In order to hold them together in a nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.86,0:25:45.03,English1,,0,0,0,,you need other particles called neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.07,0:25:49.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Their job is to keep the protons\Nfrom getting out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.11,0:25:54.01,English1,,0,0,0,,They overwhelm the protons
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.11,0:25:57.35,English1,,0,0,0,,A nucleus with two protons is element number two,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.38,0:26:00.01,English1,,0,0,0,,otherwise known as helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:03.05,English1,,0,0,0,,A nucleus with six protons is element number six,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.09,0:26:05.02,English1,,0,0,0,,which is carbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.05,0:26:08.16,English1,,0,0,0,,the fundamental building block of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.19,0:26:11.33,English1,,0,0,0,,The nucleus of a gold atom has 79 protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.36,0:26:15.16,English1,,0,0,0,,They attract 79 electrons in clouds around it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.23,0:26:17.50,English1,,0,0,0,,The way light interacts with those electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.53,0:26:20.10,English1,,0,0,0,,is what makes gold glitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.13,0:26:23.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Every additional proton in the nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.10,0:26:26.37,English1,,0,0,0,,requires enough neutrons to bind them together...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.40,0:26:28.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Up to a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.07,0:26:31.97,English1,,0,0,0,,There's an upper limit to the number of neutrons\Nyou can stuff into a nucleus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.04,0:26:33.81,English1,,0,0,0,,before it becomes unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.81,0:26:35.98,English1,,0,0,0,,I know a place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.98,0:26:38.05,English1,,0,0,0,,where the nuclei of different atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.05,0:26:40.05,English1,,0,0,0,,actually do touch each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.10,0:27:02.61,English1,,0,0,0,,The sun looks like a solid object,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.61,0:27:04.81,English1,,0,0,0,,but it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.81,0:27:07.74,English1,,0,0,0,,It's so hot that all its atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.75,0:27:09.65,English1,,0,0,0,,are always in their gaseous state.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.65,0:27:12.78,English1,,0,0,0,,The bonds that join atoms\Nto make solids and liquids on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.85,0:27:17.65,English1,,0,0,0,,are not strong enough to withstand\Nthe heat of the broiling sun
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.72,0:27:22.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Those arcing streams of incandescent gas\Nthat dwarf the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.79,0:27:27.93,English1,,0,0,0,,are guided by magnetic lines of force\Nthat emanate from below the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:30.53,English1,,0,0,0,,Why is the sun so hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.53,0:27:32.83,English1,,0,0,0,,Because its own stupendous gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.84,0:27:35.27,English1,,0,0,0,,is squeezing its atoms together.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.64,0:27:40.28,English1,,0,0,0,,The energy of gravity is being transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.28,0:27:42.41,English1,,0,0,0,,into the energy of moving atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.41,0:27:45.11,English1,,0,0,0,,That's what heat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.11,0:27:46.98,English1,,0,0,0,,The deeper we go into the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.98,0:27:48.78,English1,,0,0,0,,the greater the squeezing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.78,0:27:51.05,English1,,0,0,0,,and the higher the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.05,0:27:52.62,English1,,0,0,0,,In the heart of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.62,0:28:00.46,English1,,0,0,0,,the atoms are moving so fast that when they collide,\Nthey fuse. Their nuclei touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.46,0:28:03.90,English1,,0,0,0,,The sun is a nuclear fusion reactor,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.90,0:28:06.17,English1,,0,0,0,,held together by its own gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.17,0:28:12.70,English1,,0,0,0,,It's balanced between the inward pull of gravity\Nand the outward push of its hot gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.08,0:28:19.38,English1,,0,0,0,,That balance has lasted billions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.41,0:28:22.85,English1,,0,0,0,,providing stability that made possible\Nthe evolution of life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.92,0:28:25.32,English1,,0,0,0,,In the sun's core,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.35,0:28:27.22,English1,,0,0,0,,the fusion of hydrogen into helium
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.25,0:28:30.39,English1,,0,0,0,,releases nuclear energy in the form of photons.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.42,0:28:32.06,English1,,0,0,0,,These particles of light
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.09,0:28:33.99,English1,,0,0,0,,slowly work their way to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.03,0:28:35.73,English1,,0,0,0,,where they're seen as sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.76,0:28:39.67,English1,,0,0,0,,Helium is the ash of the sun's nuclear furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.67,0:28:43.50,English1,,0,0,0,,The sun is a medium-sized star.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.54,0:28:47.14,English1,,0,0,0,,Its core is only a lukewarm ten million degrees...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.17,0:28:48.47,English1,,0,0,0,,hot enough to fuse hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.51,0:28:50.48,English1,,0,0,0,,but too cold to fuse helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.51,0:28:52.88,English1,,0,0,0,,There are many stars in the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.91,0:28:54.48,English1,,0,0,0,,that get much hotter,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.51,0:28:56.01,English1,,0,0,0,,because they're more massive
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.05,0:28:57.58,English1,,0,0,0,,and have more gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.62,0:29:00.75,English1,,0,0,0,,Such stars fuse helium into heavier elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.79,0:29:02.72,English1,,0,0,0,,like carbon and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.75,0:29:04.66,English1,,0,0,0,,In their old age,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.69,0:29:07.36,English1,,0,0,0,,they gently diffuse these elements into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.76,0:29:11.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Other stars, more massive yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.96,0:29:14.23,English1,,0,0,0,,live fast and die young
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.27,0:29:16.23,English1,,0,0,0,,in cataclysmic supernova explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.27,0:29:19.44,English1,,0,0,0,,In our galaxy, such stars go supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.47,0:29:20.87,English1,,0,0,0,,about once a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.31,0:29:25.94,English1,,0,0,0,,These explosions are far hotter than the core of the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.98,0:29:28.88,English1,,0,0,0,,hot enough to transform elements like iron
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.91,0:29:31.25,English1,,0,0,0,,into all the heavier ones
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.28,0:29:34.45,English1,,0,0,0,,and spew them into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.49,0:29:36.35,English1,,0,0,0,,The large magellanic cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.39,0:29:38.56,English1,,0,0,0,,is a neighboring galaxy of our milky way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.59,0:29:41.22,English1,,0,0,0,,It's visible in the skies of the Southern hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.33,0:29:43.89,English1,,0,0,0,,When a supernova explodes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.93,0:29:45.46,English1,,0,0,0,,its brightness rivals
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.50,0:29:48.83,English1,,0,0,0,,that of its entire galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.58,0:30:04.31,English1,,0,0,0,,But all that light is only about one percent\Nof the energy liberated in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.41,0:30:07.48,English1,,0,0,0,,The rest of the energy is\Ncarried off by the most common
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.52,0:30:09.82,English1,,0,0,0,,and the most mysterious particles in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.85,0:30:13.22,English1,,0,0,0,,There are trillions of them\Npassing through you right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.26,0:30:15.76,English1,,0,0,0,,and yet tracking down even one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.79,0:30:19.43,English1,,0,0,0,,will take us to one of the strangest places on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.03,0:30:29.09,English1,,0,0,0,,Stalking the wild neutrino
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.13,0:30:30.93,English1,,0,0,0,,is the rarest of sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.96,0:30:35.20,English1,,0,0,0,,The lengths one must go to track them down\Nis nothing short of astonishing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.30,0:30:38.94,English1,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Super Kamiokande,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.97,0:30:42.77,English1,,0,0,0,,the subterranean Japanese neutrino detection chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.81,0:30:45.94,English1,,0,0,0,,We're more than a half mile beneath earth's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.98,0:30:48.21,English1,,0,0,0,,You might ask, "well, who in their right mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.25,0:30:51.45,English1,,0,0,0,,would bury an astronomical observatory\Nso far underground?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.48,0:30:55.02,English1,,0,0,0,,Those who hunt the most elusive prey in the cosmos:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.05,0:30:57.02,English1,,0,0,0,,The neutrino.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.05,0:30:59.02,English1,,0,0,0,,This enormous array of light detectors
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.06,0:31:02.09,English1,,0,0,0,,surrounding 50,000 tons of distilled water
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.13,0:31:05.60,English1,,0,0,0,,is a trap designed to catch neutrinos only.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:08.03,English1,,0,0,0,,Other particles, such as cosmic rays...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.06,0:31:11.03,English1,,0,0,0,,mostly protons and electrons\Nthat rain down from space...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.07,0:31:13.64,English1,,0,0,0,,cannot get through all that rock above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.67,0:31:17.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But matter poses no obstacle to a neutrino.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.07,0:31:21.08,English1,,0,0,0,,A neutrino could pass through 100 light-years of steel
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.11,0:31:23.55,English1,,0,0,0,,without even slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.58,0:31:26.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Neutrinos hardly interact with matter at all
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.32,0:31:29.58,English1,,0,0,0,,That's why you need so much of it\Nto catch even one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.62,0:31:31.65,English1,,0,0,0,,On those rare occasions when a neutrino
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.69,0:31:34.42,English1,,0,0,0,,actually does collide with a particle of ordinary matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.46,0:31:38.63,English1,,0,0,0,,it produces a ghostly, ring-shaped flash of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.66,0:31:41.33,English1,,0,0,0,,We're lying in wait
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.36,0:31:44.93,English1,,0,0,0,,for a particle that weighs next to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.97,0:31:46.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Even the miniscule electron
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.97,0:31:49.94,English1,,0,0,0,,has more than a million times its mass...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.97,0:31:51.64,English1,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.67,0:31:56.14,English1,,0,0,0,,When the supernova in the large magellanic cloud\Nblew its top in 1987
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.18,0:31:59.08,English1,,0,0,0,,this is what it would have looked like in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.11,0:32:01.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Now remember, the large magellanic cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.55,0:32:02.85,English1,,0,0,0,,is in our Southern hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.88,0:32:04.45,English1,,0,0,0,,so the neutrinos didn't come through
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.49,0:32:06.09,English1,,0,0,0,,that half-mile of rock above us,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.12,0:32:08.69,English1,,0,0,0,,they had to pass through the thousands of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.72,0:32:11.53,English1,,0,0,0,,of rock and iron below us to reach this detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.56,0:32:14.19,English1,,0,0,0,,But the coolest thing\Nwas that those neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.23,0:32:18.83,English1,,0,0,0,,hit earth three hours before\Nthe light from the supernova did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.90,0:32:21.10,English1,,0,0,0,,If nothing can travel faster than light,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.14,0:32:23.54,English1,,0,0,0,,how could that possibly be?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.14,0:32:32.01,English1,,0,0,0,,This is a dead star walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.05,0:32:37.91,English1,,0,0,0,,It may look normal, but deep within it\Nsomething cataclysmic is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.02,0:32:40.35,English1,,0,0,0,,This blue super giant star
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.39,0:32:44.82,English1,,0,0,0,,has already begun to explode inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.43,0:32:52.00,English1,,0,0,0,,Like rats deserting\Na sinking ship, the neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.03,0:32:54.50,English1,,0,0,0,,produced in the heart of the exploding star
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.53,0:32:57.07,English1,,0,0,0,,race outward at near the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.10,0:33:01.07,English1,,0,0,0,,through overlying mass in only a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.11,0:33:03.31,English1,,0,0,0,,But the shock wave of the exploding gas
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.34,0:33:06.34,English1,,0,0,0,,plods along from the center of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.38,0:33:08.98,English1,,0,0,0,,at 1/10,000 the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.01,0:33:11.22,English1,,0,0,0,,until it finally reaches
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.25,0:33:12.68,English1,,0,0,0,,the star's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.72,0:33:16.45,English1,,0,0,0,,turning it into supernova 1987a.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.56,0:33:24.23,English1,,0,0,0,,It took hours for the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.26,0:33:26.83,English1,,0,0,0,,to reach the surface of the star and blow it wide open,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.87,0:33:28.97,English1,,0,0,0,,exposing the super hot core.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.00,0:33:31.74,English1,,0,0,0,,The neutrinos had an insurmountable head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.77,0:33:37.57,English1,,0,0,0,,That's why the flash of light arrived on earth\Nso much later than the shower of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.61,0:33:41.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Before anyone had ever snared the wild neutrino,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.08,0:33:44.95,English1,,0,0,0,,it existed in the mind of a theoretical physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.98,0:33:48.02,English1,,0,0,0,,Just as Charles Darwin knew
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.05,0:33:52.62,English1,,0,0,0,,there must be an extremely long-nosed creature\Nflying around somewhere in Madagascar
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.66,0:33:56.49,English1,,0,0,0,,a 20th-century physicist named Wolfgang Pauli...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.50,0:34:01.43,English1,,0,0,0,,was desperately seeking a particle
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.47,0:34:03.73,English1,,0,0,0,,to rescue one of the pillars of modern physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.77,0:34:07.10,English1,,0,0,0,,the law of the conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.95,0:34:17.98,English1,,0,0,0,,So why didn't I flinch?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.01,0:34:22.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Because the laws of science differ fundamentally\Nfrom those of other human endeavors
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.15,0:34:25.65,English1,,0,0,0,,In order for an idea to become a scientific law,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.69,0:34:27.49,English1,,0,0,0,,it has to unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.52,0:34:30.26,English1,,0,0,0,,That's why I was willing to bet this face
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.29,0:34:33.16,English1,,0,0,0,,on the laws of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.20,0:34:35.60,English1,,0,0,0,,Now, if you try this at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.63,0:34:38.60,English1,,0,0,0,,take care not to give the cannonball a push.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.63,0:34:40.23,English1,,0,0,0,,That's adding energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.27,0:34:42.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and the ball will surely\Ncome back and do some damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.84,0:34:45.84,English1,,0,0,0,,You just have to let it go, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.04,0:34:48.34,English1,,0,0,0,,By lifting the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.38,0:34:50.08,English1,,0,0,0,,you give it gravitational energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.11,0:34:53.08,English1,,0,0,0,,which is the potential\Nto fall and accelerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.11,0:34:56.25,English1,,0,0,0,,The cannonball is going fastest\Nwhen it's at the bottom of its arc
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.35,0:34:57.99,English1,,0,0,0,,and at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.02,0:35:02.19,English1,,0,0,0,,it's converted all of its gravitational energy\Nto the energy of motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.29,0:35:04.96,English1,,0,0,0,,As it swings, the cannonball\Nis constantly exchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.99,0:35:07.19,English1,,0,0,0,,one of these two kinds of energy for the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.23,0:35:10.43,English1,,0,0,0,,but the total amount of energy remains constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.46,0:35:13.80,English1,,0,0,0,,That's an example of the\Nlaw of conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.83,0:35:16.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Once the cannonball is released,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.30,0:35:19.34,English1,,0,0,0,,it can never gain more energy\Nthan it had to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.37,0:35:22.68,English1,,0,0,0,,It has no way to fly up and break my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.71,0:35:26.68,English1,,0,0,0,,The energy accounting books\Nare always strictly balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.71,0:35:29.05,English1,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.08,0:35:30.88,English1,,0,0,0,,So in the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.92,0:35:34.29,English1,,0,0,0,,when physicists first calculated\Nthe energy of atoms precisely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.32,0:35:35.55,English1,,0,0,0,,they were startled to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.59,0:35:38.09,English1,,0,0,0,,an apparent violation of this law.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.19,0:35:42.66,English1,,0,0,0,,They found that in some radioactive atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.70,0:35:46.06,English1,,0,0,0,,the nucleus can spontaneously eject an electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.10,0:35:49.64,English1,,0,0,0,,This transforms the atom\Ninto a different element.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.67,0:35:52.20,English1,,0,0,0,,The physicists were mystified.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.24,0:35:54.31,English1,,0,0,0,,The energy of the escaped electron
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.34,0:35:56.31,English1,,0,0,0,,plus that of the new element
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.34,0:35:59.64,English1,,0,0,0,,adds up to less than the energy\Nin the original nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.68,0:36:01.55,English1,,0,0,0,,But the law says,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.58,0:36:04.48,English1,,0,0,0,,"thou shall not destroy or create energy."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.52,0:36:07.35,English1,,0,0,0,,So where did the missing energy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.39,0:36:09.52,English1,,0,0,0,,In 1930...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.56,0:36:12.09,English1,,0,0,0,,Wolfgang Pauli predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.12,0:36:14.23,English1,,0,0,0,,there must be an undiscovered particle,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.26,0:36:16.69,English1,,0,0,0,,one that makes off with the missing energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.73,0:36:19.50,English1,,0,0,0,,At the time, Pauli lamented
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.53,0:36:22.93,English1,,0,0,0,,that such a phantom particle might be so minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.97,0:36:24.87,English1,,0,0,0,,swift and evasive
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.90,0:36:27.94,English1,,0,0,0,,as to forever defy detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.97,0:36:31.37,English1,,0,0,0,,But that was a rare failure\Nof his imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.41,0:36:33.58,English1,,0,0,0,,because science is always searching
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.61,0:36:35.45,English1,,0,0,0,,for a way to go deeper still.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.48,0:36:37.38,English1,,0,0,0,,A generation later,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.42,0:36:39.75,English1,,0,0,0,,Pauli's neutrinos were actually\Ndetected for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.78,0:36:42.35,English1,,0,0,0,,in radiation from a nuclear reactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.39,0:36:46.29,English1,,0,0,0,,And we've been finding them,\Nwith difficulty, ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.32,0:36:49.19,English1,,0,0,0,,There are scientists today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.23,0:36:52.46,English1,,0,0,0,,who are trying to find a way to ride those neutrinos
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.50,0:36:56.00,English1,,0,0,0,,all the way back to the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.50,0:37:03.37,English1,,0,0,0,,We'll go as far as they have gone\Nto come up against the wall of forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.40,0:37:13.14,English1,,0,0,0,,The wall of forever is nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.17,0:37:15.11,English1,,0,0,0,,Our ancestors came up against it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.14,0:37:18.24,English1,,0,0,0,,almost as soon as they first started imagining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.28,0:37:23.05,English1,,0,0,0,,A million dawns ago, in the 13th century bc,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.08,0:37:26.58,English1,,0,0,0,,the Egyptian built this temple at Abu Simbel
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.62,0:37:28.65,English1,,0,0,0,,to honor the Pharaoh Ramses II,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.69,0:37:31.89,English1,,0,0,0,,depicted here in four colossal statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.92,0:37:37.82,English1,,0,0,0,,Reigning even above even this mighty king\Nis the falcon-headed Ra-Harakhti
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:40.10,English1,,0,0,0,,God of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.54,0:37:48.34,English1,,0,0,0,,The temple was designed so that\Nthe light from the rising sun
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.44,0:37:52.74,English1,,0,0,0,,could only enter the sanctuary\Non two days every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.78,0:37:55.78,English1,,0,0,0,,As the rays enter the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.81,0:37:59.45,English1,,0,0,0,,they burnish the statues of the gods\Nwith their golden light
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.45,0:38:03.42,English1,,0,0,0,,before penetrating the sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.45,0:38:07.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Even then, one God remains in shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.46,0:38:09.93,English1,,0,0,0,,Ptah, lord of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.96,0:38:15.06,English1,,0,0,0,,as if the origin of the universe\Nmust forever be concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.74,0:38:21.54,English1,,0,0,0,,Feel the sun on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.57,0:38:24.14,English1,,0,0,0,,The energy that warms you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.17,0:38:27.31,English1,,0,0,0,,began its journey some ten million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.34,0:38:29.44,English1,,0,0,0,,in the heart of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.48,0:38:32.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Unlike neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.55,0:38:34.35,English1,,0,0,0,,the photons needed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.38,0:38:37.35,English1,,0,0,0,,that long to work their way out\Nfrom the core to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.39,0:38:39.39,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.42,0:38:43.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Because they were colliding billions\Nof times per second with the sun's atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.76,0:38:47.63,English1,,0,0,0,,every collision sending them off in a random direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.66,0:38:49.63,English1,,0,0,0,,But once they finally reached the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.66,0:38:52.76,English1,,0,0,0,,they were free to dash nonstop, at the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.84,0:38:57.84,English1,,0,0,0,,in a mere eight minutes and 20 seconds\Nfrom the sun to you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.57,0:39:02.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Ten-million-year-old light on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.08,0:39:10.75,English1,,0,0,0,,What was happening\Nwhen that light left the heart of the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.62,0:39:18.66,English1,,0,0,0,,The cosmic calendar compresses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.69,0:39:21.49,English1,,0,0,0,,the entire 13.8 billion year history
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.53,0:39:23.60,English1,,0,0,0,,of the universe into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.63,0:39:27.17,English1,,0,0,0,,Every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.20,0:39:30.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Every day, about 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.10,0:39:33.34,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe is so old that,\Non the cosmic calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.37,0:39:37.11,English1,,0,0,0,,ten million years ago\Nonly takes us back as far as...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.14,0:39:43.55,English1,,0,0,0,,6:00 P.M. on the last evening\Nof the last day of the year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.65,0:39:45.22,English1,,0,0,0,,And what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.25,0:39:47.09,English1,,0,0,0,,Humans had yet to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.12,0:39:48.85,English1,,0,0,0,,Ten million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.89,0:39:51.29,English1,,0,0,0,,our ancestors were anthropoid apes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.32,0:39:53.22,English1,,0,0,0,,swinging through the trees of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.26,0:39:56.73,English1,,0,0,0,,To us, ten million years\Nseems like a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.76,0:39:59.13,English1,,0,0,0,,but it's only the length of an afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.17,0:40:01.63,English1,,0,0,0,,on the timescale of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.97,0:40:09.87,English1,,0,0,0,,The sun began fusing hydrogen\N4,500 million years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.94,0:40:13.64,English1,,0,0,0,,August 31 on the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.68,0:40:15.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Our milky way galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.75,0:40:18.82,English1,,0,0,0,,is about 10,000 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.85,0:40:23.92,English1,,0,0,0,,The first galaxies formed about\Na few billion years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.96,0:40:27.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Something keeps me from going\Nany further back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.93,0:40:29.93,English1,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.60,0:40:35.47,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the nature of light and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.50,0:40:38.67,English1,,0,0,0,,Because light travels at a finite speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.70,0:40:43.67,English1,,0,0,0,,to look across space is to look back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:48.75,English1,,0,0,0,,So the farther we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.78,0:40:51.58,English1,,0,0,0,,the older the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.62,0:40:56.42,English1,,0,0,0,,This is as far back in the history of\Nthe cosmos as we can see with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.45,0:40:58.85,English1,,0,0,0,,It's a baby picture of universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.89,0:41:01.96,English1,,0,0,0,,when it was only 380,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.99,0:41:07.56,English1,,0,0,0,,That's 15 minutes into January 1\Non the cosmic calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.66,0:41:12.80,English1,,0,0,0,,If we look as far as we can see in any direction\Nusing microwave telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.84,0:41:14.27,English1,,0,0,0,,this is what we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.30,0:41:17.61,English1,,0,0,0,,the glow left over from the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.64,0:41:21.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Imagine that all the matter and energy\Nof the observable universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.54,0:41:25.78,English1,,0,0,0,,was concentrated into something\Nno larger than this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.85,0:41:29.72,English1,,0,0,0,,That's the size of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.75,0:41:35.02,English1,,0,0,0,,when it was a trillionth of a trillionth\Nof a trillionth of a second old
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.16,0:41:38.69,English1,,0,0,0,,All the matter and energy\Nof the hundred billion galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.73,0:41:41.80,English1,,0,0,0,,now splayed out across\Nthe billions of light-years
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.83,0:41:46.10,English1,,0,0,0,,were once pent up in something the size of a marble
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.20,0:41:50.14,English1,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how tightly packed\Nthat marble must have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.17,0:41:53.01,English1,,0,0,0,,Far too dense for any kind\Nof light to move through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.04,0:41:56.81,English1,,0,0,0,,but no obstacle for the likes of neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.84,0:41:59.71,English1,,0,0,0,,The big bang must have produced stupendous\Nnumbers of neutrinos,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.75,0:42:03.41,English1,,0,0,0,,which flew unhindered through\Nthat inconceivable crush of matter
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.45,0:42:06.65,English1,,0,0,0,,The very thing that makes them\Nalmost impossible to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.69,0:42:13.36,English1,,0,0,0,,is what allows neutrinos to sail through the curtain\Nthat conceals the beginning of time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.46,0:42:15.03,English1,,0,0,0,,Where are they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.06,0:42:16.60,English1,,0,0,0,,They are here, they're there,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.63,0:42:18.83,English1,,0,0,0,,everywhere throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.87,0:42:21.70,English1,,0,0,0,,Neutrinos from creation are within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.77,0:42:25.00,English1,,0,0,0,,From a marble...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:27.04,English1,,0,0,0,,To the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:43.89,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the road that Thales\Nand Democritus put us on some 2,500 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.92,0:42:45.96,English1,,0,0,0,,a road of endless searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.99,0:42:49.29,English1,,0,0,0,,a relentless, systematic hunt for new worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.33,0:42:51.96,English1,,0,0,0,,and an ever-deepening understanding of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.43,0:43:00.00,English1,,0,0,0,,Who among you will pick up that torch\Nand take us down that next stretch of road?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.48,0:43:07.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Sync and corrections by oykubuyuk\Nwww.addic7ed.com
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.86,0:00:05.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,除了我们生活的这个层次  还有其他的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.46,0:00:10.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到处充满了隐藏着的其他维度
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:12.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从许多光年以外
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到我们的脚下
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.94,0:00:17.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,甚至在我们的体内
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.58,0:00:20.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们由原子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:23.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们眼睛中的原子数量
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:27.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比已知宇宙中所有星系的星星数量还多
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.04,0:00:34.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上述情况也适用于任何
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.21,0:00:36.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比你的指尖稍大的实体
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:40.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我由30万亿亿亿复杂排列的原子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我是名叫尼尔·德葛拉司·泰森的原子组合体
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:48.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们也是一样  只是名字不同
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.63,0:00:50.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们通常不会这么认为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.16,0:00:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为这个级别的存在超过了我们感官的范畴
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:00:56.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们不会就此停止
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.47,0:00:59.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们还要继续探究
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子使所有事情变得有生气
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:49.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要了解水 你需要知道它的原子规律
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.76,0:02:52.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个水分子都是由
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:53.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两个小小的氢原子
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.87,0:02:56.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,附着在一个大的氧原子上组成
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.54,0:02:58.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此我们称之为 一氧化二氢
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.64,0:03:01.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果温度不冷不热
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分子们可以相互翻滚穿行
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.48,0:03:06.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分子间虽然有一些粘滞性
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.78,0:03:10.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是不足以让它们变得紧密
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.05,0:03:12.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是液体的特性
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.82,0:03:14.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳将水加热
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.49,0:03:15.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,给它更多的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.89,0:03:17.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分子们移动加快
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.83,0:03:19.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,温度就是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.63,0:03:21.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当分子运到快到足以
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:24.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,打破彼此间脆弱的联系时
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:26.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是蒸发
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.70,0:03:28.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们呼吸的空气
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:30.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是由氮和氧的分子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:34.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,再加一些水蒸气和二氧化碳
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.47,0:03:36.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,小心
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:38.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是冷凝
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.75,0:03:41.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,露珠就是冷凝战胜蒸发
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.35,0:03:43.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的胜利果实
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.48,0:03:45.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种现象持续下去
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.25,0:03:48.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就是一个小宇宙 包含它自己的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:51.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生物 戏剧性的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:55.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了探索这滴露珠的广阔领域
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:56.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们需要一艘船
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:00.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,配上两种引擎
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学和想象力
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.51,0:04:10.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是单细胞的草履虫
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:13.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,众多娴熟的猎人之一
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:15.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在露珠中游荡
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.88,0:04:18.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是它们也是猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:23.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长颈虫  草履虫的死敌
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:26.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,草履虫或许可以幸运的直接击杀
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:28.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就算不能
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:31.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,齐射攻击造成的后座力拉开了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:32.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,草履虫与攻击者之间的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没什么可说的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.03,0:04:39.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是露珠内的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.88,0:04:54.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那个小家伙是水熊虫
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:57.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一种比针尖还小的动物
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.22,0:05:02.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可别小看它
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:04.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,水熊虫在这个星球上的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:05.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比我们的还长久
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.56,0:05:08.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约5亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.80,0:05:12.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和我们的数量比例
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.84,0:05:16.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,至少是1比10亿
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.07,0:05:21.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们可以在地球上任何地方生存
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.41,0:05:25.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在最高的寒冷的山峰顶端
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在喷发的火山口里
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.95,0:05:29.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大洋的底部
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,水熊虫是如此的坚强
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.92,0:05:32.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们可以在
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真空中生存
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.36,0:05:36.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们经历了最近
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:38.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,5次的大灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.03,0:05:42.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果外星人认为地球是水熊虫的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.33,0:05:45.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是绝对可以原谅的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.47,0:05:53.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果还要看这滴露珠的其他地方 最好继续往前走
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.94,0:05:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每片叶子和苔藓
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都有成千上万的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.12,0:06:03.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显微镜才能看见的嘴巴 称为气孔
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.62,0:06:05.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,植物通过它们呼吸
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:07.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸入二氧化碳
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:09.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呼出我们赖以生存的氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:12.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球上可以没有我们
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.33,0:06:14.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们还有其他动物
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:17.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,离开它们就死翘翘了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球通过阳光获取食物
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.97,0:06:22.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们动物做不到
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:24.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想看它们是怎么做到的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.34,0:06:25.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们还要潜的更深
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:27.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把我们变小大约1千倍
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.97,0:06:30.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才能进入它们的宝库
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:32.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们把好东西都藏在里面
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.51,0:06:34.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,叶绿素
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:35.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是个分子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.88,0:06:38.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把阳光转换成能量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.89,0:06:44.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个长方形都是一个植物细胞
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:46.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有那些小绿车
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:48.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是它的能量工厂
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.99,0:06:50.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们可以窃取它们的商业机密
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:53.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又能带来一次崭新的工业革命
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.17,0:06:54.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是要偷窥它们
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:56.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们还要潜的更深
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:11.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想象之舟这次又要将我们带去
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.09,0:07:13.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪个截然不同的世界呢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:15.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它是个宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:19.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包含在露珠内的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们现在做的就是工业间谍活动
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.23,0:07:24.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果想刺探叶绿体的商业机密
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.70,0:07:27.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,叶绿体里的制作过程
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:30.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就当我们的全部未来就靠它了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.44,0:07:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,叶绿体利用阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.71,0:07:35.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将水分子
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:37.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分解成氢原子和氧原子
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:40.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将氢气与二氧化碳结合
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.22,0:07:41.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生糖
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:45.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将氧气作为废气排出
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:48.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要一探究竟 我们还要潜的更深
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:49.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变得更小
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.76,0:07:52.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,小到原子级别
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:54.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,成功了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:56.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这条流水线是分子工业基地
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:07:58.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的核心
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:00.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在分子这个级别
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:02.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,速度快到我们看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:04.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我们必须让它们慢下来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.81,0:08:07.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,放慢10亿倍
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:11.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些大分子就是二氧化碳
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.98,0:08:13.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每一个分子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.48,0:08:15.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由1个碳原子和2个氧原子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.38,0:08:18.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当阳光照射叶绿素的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:21.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生一系列的化学反应
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分解水分子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.59,0:08:26.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,释放活泼的电子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.63,0:08:30.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这只是白班的活
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:33.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只在日光注入能量时工作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.17,0:08:36.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一组不分昼夜的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.14,0:08:38.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,利用预留的太阳能工作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:43.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自由电子的能量开始工作了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:47.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将二氧化碳与水中的氢结合
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:52.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生糖  用以储存太阳能
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.15,0:08:55.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,叶绿体从事太阳能采集工作
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:57.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,达30亿年之久
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.66,0:09:00.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,微观世界的太阳能电池
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:02.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,驱动所有的森林 田地
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海中的浮游生物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:06.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有动物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.93,0:09:08.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括我们
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳能的生物圈
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.34,0:09:16.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比我们整个人类文明收集并处理的能量多出6倍
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.88,0:09:18.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们了解化学层面的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.81,0:09:20.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光合作用工作原理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:22.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们可以在实验室复制这样的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:25.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们做不到植物这么好
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.45,0:09:27.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这不奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:29.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大自然已经干了几十亿年了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.95,0:09:32.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们才刚开始
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.06,0:09:33.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们可以知道
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.62,0:09:35.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光合作用的商业机密
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.89,0:09:39.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如今我们赖以生存的其他形式的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:42.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,煤 石油 天然气
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都可以淘汰了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.90,0:09:47.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光合作用是终极绿色能源
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不会污染大气
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:51.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上 碳中和
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:54.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人造光合作用可以很大程度上
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:56.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,减少温室效应
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.88,0:10:00.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,温室效应恶化了气候变化
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:02.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里开始蒸发了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.59,0:10:04.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,该撤了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.66,0:10:09.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,露珠的生命一闪即逝
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.16,0:10:12.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在寒冷的夜里从稀薄的空气中凝结而成
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:14.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却在日出之后无影无踪
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.53,0:10:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的居民怎么办 水熊虫呢
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:19.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没事的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:21.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们可以几年不喝水
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.67,0:10:24.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很难想象
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.57,0:10:26.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,覆盖地球表面的植物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:29.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几亿年后
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:32.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才开出第一朵花
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.51,0:10:35.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约1亿年前
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:38.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恐龙灭绝前不久
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:42.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时世界的颜色一定很单调
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:45.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有绿色和褐色
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:49.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是有大树和蕨类 还有其他的植物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.86,0:10:52.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是没有紫色的鸢尾花
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:55.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也没有大红色的玫瑰花
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:04.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,兰花是最早出现的花之一
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:08.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在它们有着最多的品种
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.32,0:11:13.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,达尔文特别痴迷
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.59,0:11:15.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,马达加斯加的彗星兰
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.46,0:11:19.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种花的花粉藏在一条又长又细的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.06,0:11:23.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,花径底部
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:26.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,预测能力是验证一种理论
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:28.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最好的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据他的物竞天择
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.07,0:11:31.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的进化论基础
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:34.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,达尔文推测
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.17,0:11:37.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在马达加斯加岛上 一定有一种会飞的昆虫
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:41.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长着非常长的舌头
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:42.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长的足够接触到那些花粉
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:46.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从没人看过这种动物
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:48.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是达尔文坚信
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.32,0:11:51.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,肯定有这样的动物存在
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:53.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时相信他的人不多
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.43,0:11:56.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到50多年后
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:11:59.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才证明了达尔文的正确
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:04.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1903年 有一种被称为马岛长喙天蛾的蛾子
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.87,0:12:06.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在马达加斯加被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:10.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,受到彗星兰花粉香味的吸引
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:14.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这蛾子用它1英尺长的口器吸食花粉
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:16.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和达尔文预测的一样
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:24.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更令人惊奇的是 发现这种蛾子时
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.86,0:12:27.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,马达加斯加岛上超过90%
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.29,0:12:30.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的雨林已经遭到破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:33.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在达尔文著名的猜测多年后
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.50,0:12:36.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种蛾子很有可能已经灭绝
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:39.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就和其他同类一样
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.50,0:12:42.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们每一个都是生命诗篇中的独特乐章
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:46.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由万古的进化写在原子中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.38,0:12:54.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,丁香花的芬芳
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种香味
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.35,0:12:59.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让人不禁浮想翩翩
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:02.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很久前的每个夏天都是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎会如此
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.36,0:13:07.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,味道是怎么会让你的头脑中出现影像的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:09.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那不是我们能看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.77,0:13:12.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有可能是象光一样的能量波吗
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:15.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还是一种微观粒子呢
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:17.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其实它是一种分子
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.24,0:13:21.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每种味道 不论是来自烤焦的面包
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.04,0:13:24.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还是汽油 或者一片丁香花
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:26.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是一大片的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些分子有种特定的形状
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:32.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我吸入它们时
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们刺激我鼻子中一组特定的感受细胞
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:40.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一种电子信号传递到我的大脑
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.80,0:13:43.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,告诉我这个味道是丁香花的香味
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:48.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不同的分子携带不同的味道
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.90,0:13:51.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形状各异
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.57,0:13:54.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但当我闻到一朵花 或者篝火
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:13:56.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者机器的润滑油
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:59.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通常是涌现出大量的记忆
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:04.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么花香这么简单的东西能够引起
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:07.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,强烈的记忆呢
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.09,0:14:13.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一定和我们的大脑进化方式有关
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.59,0:14:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当大脑中的嗅神经受到刺激
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.96,0:14:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的嗅觉开始工作
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.33,0:14:23.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种神经就在扁桃体旁边
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:28.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是我们情感体验的组成部分
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.64,0:14:31.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也很靠近海马体
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生记忆的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:39.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,神经网络将气味信号
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:42.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从我的鼻子传递到
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.69,0:14:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我这经过上亿年进化的大脑
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.86,0:14:50.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一种生存机制 给我们发出警告
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:53.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们避开危险
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:57.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你能提前发觉猎食者
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:15:00.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他发动攻击前
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:03.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者在被大火困在森林前
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.01,0:15:05.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就会大大增加你的生存几率
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:08.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后把你的基因传给下一代
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.79,0:15:16.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,花田里的迷人芬芳
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:19.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发出一组独特的神经信号密码
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:22.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有这个密码可以打开我们大脑中
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.99,0:15:26.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,储存关于丁香花的记忆保险箱
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:33.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,啥味道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:36.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们或许以后会知道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.54,0:15:40.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但首先 还有一个隐藏着的宇宙等着我们
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:03.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,植物们静静的呼吸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:06.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸入二氧化碳分子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:08.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呼出氧气分子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:10.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和我相反
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:13.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与雪花和指纹不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:15.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同类的原子或分子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:18.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是完全的相同
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:20.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每次吸气
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:23.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们吸入的分子数量
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:26.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和已知宇宙的所有星星数量一样多
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.06,0:16:29.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呼出的气体与空气流通交换
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:31.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大地上逐渐混合
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.67,0:16:35.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让别人也可以呼吸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:36.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一起呼吸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:51.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们大致吸入了1亿的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.32,0:16:53.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些分子曾经被所有的前人
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.52,0:16:55.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呼吸过
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.59,0:16:58.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想想看 这种原子的再生
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.79,0:17:01.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将我们与远古的祖先联系在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:04.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括那些最初带领我们
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.63,0:17:06.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探索未知宇宙的人
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.80,0:17:10.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些宇宙就如同你我一样真实
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.27,0:17:12.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就在我们的身边
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:19.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,曾经我们如梦初醒
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.38,0:17:21.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开始用崭新的方法审视和思考
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:25.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是大约2500年前
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.49,0:17:27.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在希腊的小岛上
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.32,0:17:30.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,位于东方与西方文明之间
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.62,0:17:34.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,商人 游客 水手们自由的融合
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.73,0:17:37.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,交流各自关于伟人和神的传说
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:42.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在爱奥尼亚有个叫米利都的城市 就是今天的土耳其
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:44.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一些现代生活的最基本元素
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.57,0:17:47.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那里出现了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.91,0:17:55.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一次对生活形式的重现
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.21,0:17:58.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由专业人士创作并演绎
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:18:00.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,期待可以深深感动
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.02,0:18:02.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,观众的内心
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:05.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者只是逗他们开心
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.72,0:18:10.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,诞生了第一场演出 戏剧还有喜剧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.39,0:18:12.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一种极其崭新的概念
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,民治政府
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:19.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从最初模糊的不完美的概念 到如今的民主
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:23.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,普通民众也可以拥有某些权力的观念
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.84,0:18:27.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那时 在这里诞生萌芽
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:31.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在我看来 这个古代世界带给我们的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.68,0:18:35.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最革命性的创新观念是
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:41.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自然事件并不是众神给我们的惩罚或奖励
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:44.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大自然的规律不一定要用
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:47.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,超自然力量来解释
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:50.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,表达出这种观念的第一人
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:52.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,名叫 泰利斯（希腊哲学家）
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.47,0:18:54.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当闪电或地震时
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.47,0:18:59.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是因为我们的所作所为触怒了严厉的众神
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.71,0:19:02.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是一种我们可以理解的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:05.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自然过程的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:08.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管没有任何记录他原话的书籍留存下来
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:12.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,泰利斯的思想光芒依然照耀我们
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙运行的井井有条的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.96,0:19:20.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙由我们可以理解的自然法则控制的这种观念
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.36,0:19:25.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种伟大的观念在泰利斯的头脑中萌芽
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:30.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仅仅在泰利斯身后100年
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.47,0:19:32.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又一个天才出现了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.07,0:19:34.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他与众不同的是
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.41,0:19:36.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一个发现了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.64,0:19:39.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们周围未知宇宙的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:43.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来自阿夫季拉的德谟克利特是位真正的科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:47.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,充满探索宇宙激情的男人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.19,0:19:48.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也很会享受
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.99,0:19:52.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他曾说 没有狂欢的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.33,0:19:55.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像没有尽头的漫漫长路
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:57.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就样吗
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:19:59.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这么简单吗
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:01.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是虚无中的一堆原子
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.77,0:20:02.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然也
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.44,0:20:05.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你想想看
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.81,0:20:07.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个世界必然是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:10.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由虚无中无数的不可见的微粒组成
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.94,0:20:15.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,否则万物就不会移动 生长 被分离或改变
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:20.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果没有原子和容纳它们的空旷太空的话
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.45,0:20:23.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个世界会变得铁板一块 死气沉沉
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.00,0:20:26.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,别伤心了 少年
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.44,0:20:28.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想想那无尽的可能性吧
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.94,0:20:32.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由那些原子排列组合所带来的可能性
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.65,0:20:38.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,向这杯中
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.22,0:20:42.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有酒中的原子们致敬
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:44.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有它们带来的欢乐
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.79,0:20:49.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,遍布酒杯的泥土
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.86,0:20:51.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是用显微镜才能看到的矿物微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:54.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,晶体的一种
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:58.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个都有与众不同的原子结构
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.30,0:21:00.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,矿物结构很精妙
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:03.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是它们的结构形式有限
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.81,0:21:07.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一粒石英就是一个由3个相同原子组成的晶格集合体
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.08,0:21:10.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有变化 不断重复
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:16.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使是相对复杂的矿物晶格 比如黄宝石
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:18.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由10个左右的原子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.99,0:21:21.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也只是相同的原子结构
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.66,0:21:23.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不断重复
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.92,0:21:29.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了转换到另一个维度
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.99,0:21:33.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了将它从不断重复的晶格束缚中释放
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.40,0:21:37.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你需要一个可以从任何方向与其他原子相结合的原子
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.50,0:21:40.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它也要能与其他不同的原子相结合
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.84,0:21:50.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看 碳原子
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:53.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球上生命不可缺少的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:56.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为啥
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.45,0:22:01.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,碳之所以特殊是因为它可以一次与最多4种原子结合
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.19,0:22:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它可以与许多其他种类的原子结合
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.96,0:22:06.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也包括其他碳原子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:08.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它可以弯曲成环状
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.63,0:22:10.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也可以连成一条线
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.86,0:22:15.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,组成远比任何一种晶体都复杂的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.47,0:22:21.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其它原子都没有这种灵活性
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.41,0:22:23.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就算拥有类似化学属性的原子也不行
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.88,0:22:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如 硅
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.48,0:22:29.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也无法像碳这样组成丰富多样的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.65,0:22:32.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种碳基分子 我们称为 蛋白质
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.22,0:22:34.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,组成生命的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.42,0:22:37.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包含了成千上万的原子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,碳原子是世界上一切生物分子的支柱
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.83,0:22:46.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括我们
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.33,0:22:49.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是岩石和生物的区别
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:53.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命可以制造出大量的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.67,0:22:56.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有着惊人体积和复杂性的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.18,0:22:58.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自由自在地随机应变
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.31,0:23:00.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进化
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.34,0:23:02.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,甚至 爱
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.30,0:23:35.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,放轻松
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.37,0:23:37.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他并没有真的碰到的她
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:39.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,日常生活中
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:41.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以原子这个层面上来说
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.58,0:23:45.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物体绝对不会接触
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.48,0:23:48.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个原子的中心都有一个原子核
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.92,0:23:52.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被力线电子云所包围
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.32,0:23:54.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当原子彼此接近时
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.83,0:23:56.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,男孩的电子云
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.79,0:23:58.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,推开女孩的电子云
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.40,0:24:02.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,超过99.9%的原子物质
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:04.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,集中在它的原子核中
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.77,0:24:08.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核被电子云包围
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:10.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电子云形成无形的力场
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.64,0:24:12.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像减震器
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.95,0:24:15.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电子云的结构
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.62,0:24:17.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,决定了元素的本质
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.62,0:24:20.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以地球上物质的正常情况来说
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.29,0:24:22.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核不会彼此接触
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.19,0:24:24.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们有接触的感觉
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.29,0:24:26.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那只不过是看不见的力场
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.93,0:24:29.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相互重叠的同时相互排斥
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.64,0:24:48.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核非常小
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.11,0:24:49.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相较于原子的其他部分
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.78,0:24:53.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果原子像这个教堂这么大
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.82,0:24:58.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核的尺寸也就是那粒灰尘的大小
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.83,0:25:05.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子的大部分是空旷的空间
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.06,0:25:07.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了理解事物的本质
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.80,0:25:09.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们要去更深的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.80,0:25:12.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,去一个比原子还小10万倍的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.84,0:25:14.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的原子核
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.01,0:25:22.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙中最简单 但又最丰富的原子是氢原子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.48,0:25:24.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的原子核只有一个质子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.72,0:25:27.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以它在元素周期表中位于第一位
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.75,0:25:29.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,围绕它的云
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.59,0:25:34.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是它唯一的电子可以运行的范围
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.56,0:25:37.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核有两个质子时会是什么情况
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.83,0:25:39.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,质子相互排斥
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.50,0:25:41.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了让它们保持在原子核内
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.86,0:25:45.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你还需要另一种粒子 称之 中子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.07,0:25:49.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们的工作是防止质子出轨
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.11,0:25:54.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们用强大的核引力压制质子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.11,0:25:57.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核有2个质子的元素排名第2
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.38,0:26:00.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,名曰 氦
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:03.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核有6个质子的元素排名第6
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.09,0:26:05.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是碳
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.05,0:26:08.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命的基石
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.19,0:26:11.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,金元素的原子核有79个质子
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.36,0:26:15.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在周围的云中 它们吸引了79个电子
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.23,0:26:17.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光与这些电子的互动
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.53,0:26:20.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是黄金闪光的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.13,0:26:23.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核中每增加一个质子
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.10,0:26:26.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都需要有足够的中子把它们聚集在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.40,0:26:28.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在一定程度上
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.07,0:26:31.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你能塞进原子核的中子数量是有上限的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.04,0:26:33.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,否则会变得不稳定
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.81,0:26:35.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有个地方
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.98,0:26:38.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不同原子的原子核
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.05,0:26:40.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能够相互接触
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.10,0:27:02.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳看上去像个实体
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.61,0:27:04.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它不是
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.81,0:27:07.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它把所有的原子都
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.75,0:27:09.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加热到了气态
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.65,0:27:12.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球上将原子束缚产生液态和固体的粘合力
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.85,0:27:17.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不足以承受炽热太阳的热量
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.72,0:27:22.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些耀眼气体的弧形气流使地球看上去渺小
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.79,0:27:27.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,受到太阳表面之下发射出来的力场的磁力线引导
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:30.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳怎么会这么热
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.53,0:27:32.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它惊人的引力
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.84,0:27:35.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将原子们积压在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.64,0:27:40.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,引力的能量转换成
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.28,0:27:42.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,移动原子的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.41,0:27:45.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是热的来源
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.11,0:27:46.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,越到太阳的内部
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.98,0:27:48.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,挤压的力量越大
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.78,0:27:51.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,温度也越高
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.05,0:27:52.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在太阳的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.62,0:28:00.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子的移动速度快到 它们碰撞时发生融化 原子核发生接触
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.46,0:28:03.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳就是核聚变反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.90,0:28:06.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由它的引力来维系
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.17,0:28:12.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它在向内拉的引力和向外推的热浪间取得平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.08,0:28:19.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种平衡持续几十亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.41,0:28:22.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,提供了使地球上生物进化成为可能的稳定性
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.92,0:28:25.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在太阳的核心
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.35,0:28:27.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢融合后变成氦
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.25,0:28:30.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以光子的形式释放核能
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.42,0:28:32.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些光的微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.09,0:28:33.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,慢慢的来到表面
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.03,0:28:35.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是我们所见的日光
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.76,0:28:39.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氦原子就是太阳核反应的残渣
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.67,0:28:43.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳是一颗中等尺寸的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.54,0:28:47.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的核心温度只不过1千万度
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.17,0:28:48.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只够融化氢原子
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.51,0:28:50.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却不足以融化氦原子
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.51,0:28:52.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,银河系中有很多恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.91,0:28:54.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比太阳热得多
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.51,0:28:56.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们质量更大
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.05,0:28:57.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,引力更大
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.62,0:29:00.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些恒星将氦融化成更重的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.79,0:29:02.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如 碳和氧
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.75,0:29:04.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,等它们老了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.69,0:29:07.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们慢慢的将这些元素散播到太空中
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.76,0:29:11.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有些恒星 质量更大
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.96,0:29:14.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一生苦短 英年早逝
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.27,0:29:16.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卒于灾难性的超新星大爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.27,0:29:19.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的银河系中 这样的恒星变成超新星
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.47,0:29:20.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约100年一次
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.31,0:29:25.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些爆炸比太阳核心热的多得多
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.98,0:29:28.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,热的足够把铁元素
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.91,0:29:31.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成更重的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.28,0:29:34.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把它们喷向太空
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.49,0:29:36.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大麦哲伦星云
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.39,0:29:38.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是我们银河系的邻居
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.59,0:29:41.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以在南半球的星空中看到
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.33,0:29:43.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当超新星爆炸时
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.93,0:29:45.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的亮度超过
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.50,0:29:48.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的整个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.58,0:30:04.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这些光也只是爆炸产生的能量中的大约1%
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.41,0:30:07.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其它的能量化成宇宙中最常见
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.52,0:30:09.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也最神秘的微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.85,0:30:13.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在就有几万亿的这种微粒穿过你的身体
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.26,0:30:15.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而即使为了找到一个这样的微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.79,0:30:19.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也需要我们去到地球上最离奇的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.03,0:30:29.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,追踪野生的中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.13,0:30:30.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是最小众的运动
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.96,0:30:35.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,追踪它们的难度 难得令人惊讶
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.30,0:30:38.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到超级神冈探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.97,0:30:42.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,日本地下中微子探测器的内部
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.81,0:30:45.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们身处地表之下超过半英里 （大约1公里)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.98,0:30:48.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你或许会问 哪个正常人
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.25,0:30:51.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会把天文台埋在这么深的地下
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.48,0:30:55.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些人狩猎宇宙中最神出鬼没的猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.05,0:30:57.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.05,0:30:59.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个庞大的光探测器阵列
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.06,0:31:02.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,围绕着5万吨蒸馏水
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.13,0:31:05.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,设计这个陷阱只为了抓捕中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:08.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他粒子 例如宇宙射线
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.06,0:31:11.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大部分是从太空中落下的质子和电子
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.07,0:31:13.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无法穿过我们头顶的岩石
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.67,0:31:17.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这些对中微子来说都不是障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.07,0:31:21.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子可以穿过100光年厚的铁板
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.11,0:31:23.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,甚至不会减速
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.58,0:31:26.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子几乎不受其他物质影响
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.32,0:31:29.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我们需要如此大费周章
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.62,0:31:31.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在很罕见的情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.69,0:31:34.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子和其他微粒发生冲突
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.46,0:31:38.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它会产生一个幽灵般的环形闪光
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.66,0:31:41.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们守株待兔
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.36,0:31:44.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,等一个几乎没有重量的微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.97,0:31:46.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,甚至比电子
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.97,0:31:49.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还轻100万倍
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.97,0:31:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那里
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.67,0:31:56.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1987年 当大麦哲伦星云的超新星爆炸时
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.18,0:31:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是当时这里出现的景象
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.11,0:32:01.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,请记住 大麦哲伦星云
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.55,0:32:02.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我们的南半球
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.88,0:32:04.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这些中微子不是穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.49,0:32:06.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们头顶上半英里的岩石
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.12,0:32:08.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是必须穿过我们身下
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.72,0:32:11.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几千英里的岩石和铁才能到达这里
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.56,0:32:14.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是最酷的事情是
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.23,0:32:18.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子比超新星发出的光早3小时到达地球
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.90,0:32:21.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果没有什么能比光跑得快
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.14,0:32:23.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这又是怎么回事呢
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.14,0:32:32.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星之将死
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.05,0:32:37.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看上去好像挺正常 但是在它的深处大灾难已经发生
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.02,0:32:40.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这颗蓝色的超级巨大的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.39,0:32:44.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,内部即将发生爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.43,0:32:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如同即将沉船上的老鼠 慌不择路
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.03,0:32:54.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即将爆炸的恒星内部产生的中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.53,0:32:57.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以接近光速的速度向外逃逸
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.10,0:33:01.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几秒内穿过覆盖物
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.11,0:33:03.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是爆炸气体的冲击波
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.34,0:33:06.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从恒星内部缓缓踱出
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.38,0:33:08.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有光速的万分之一
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.01,0:33:11.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到最后抵达
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.25,0:33:12.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星的表面
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.72,0:33:16.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成了1987年的超新星
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.56,0:33:24.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要好几个小时
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.26,0:33:26.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爆炸才能到达表面 然后向外喷发
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.87,0:33:28.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将极度炙热的内核炸开
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.00,0:33:31.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子已经赢在了起跑线上
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.77,0:33:37.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么闪光会比中微子晚这么多到达地球
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.61,0:33:41.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在“野生”中微子被捕获前
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.08,0:33:44.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它已经存在于理论物理学家的脑海中
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.98,0:33:48.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就如同查尔斯·达尔文知道
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.05,0:33:52.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,必定有一种超级长鼻生物生活在马达加斯加
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.66,0:33:56.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一位名叫沃尔夫冈·泡利的20世纪物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.50,0:34:01.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,致力于寻找一种微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.47,0:34:03.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用来拯救现代物理学的支柱之一
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.77,0:34:07.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能量守恒定律
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.95,0:34:17.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我为什么没有退缩
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.01,0:34:22.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为科学定律与其它人类活动的根本区别
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.15,0:34:25.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要将一种设想变成科学定律
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.69,0:34:27.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,必须要无懈可击
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.52,0:34:30.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是为何我愿意赌上我的脸
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.29,0:34:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来证明能量守恒定律
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.20,0:34:35.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你在家自己尝试
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.63,0:34:38.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,千万小心不要推这个球
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.63,0:34:40.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那会增加能量
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.27,0:34:42.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这球肯定会回来造成伤害
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.84,0:34:45.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要像这样轻轻放手
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.04,0:34:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,抬起这个球
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.38,0:34:50.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你给它势能
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.11,0:34:53.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使它可能坠落并且加速
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.11,0:34:56.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,球在弧度底部时速度达到最大
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.35,0:34:57.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那个时候
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.02,0:35:02.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它把所有的势能转化成动能
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.29,0:35:04.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,摇摆时 球不断转换能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.99,0:35:07.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从一种转换到另一种
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.23,0:35:10.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是能量的总量保持不变
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.46,0:35:13.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是能量守恒定律的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.83,0:35:16.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,放开球的那刻
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.30,0:35:19.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就无法获得更多的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.37,0:35:22.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它不可能飞过来打到我的鼻子
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.71,0:35:26.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能量这笔账永远是平衡的
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.71,0:35:29.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,做不得假
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.08,0:35:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在20世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.92,0:35:34.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当科学家首次精确测量出原子的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.32,0:35:35.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们惊讶的发现了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.59,0:35:38.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,违背这个定律的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.19,0:35:42.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们发现在一些放射性原子中
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.70,0:35:46.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原子核自发的喷出一个电子
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.10,0:35:49.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将原子转变成另一种元素
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.67,0:35:52.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物理学家迷惑了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.24,0:35:54.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,逃逸电子的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.34,0:35:56.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加上新元素的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.34,0:35:59.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,少于原有原子核的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.68,0:36:01.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,定律指出
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.58,0:36:04.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能量既不会凭空产生 也不会凭空消失
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.52,0:36:07.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么那些能量去了哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.39,0:36:09.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1930年
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.56,0:36:12.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,沃尔夫冈·泡利预测
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.12,0:36:14.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一定有一种未知的微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.26,0:36:16.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带走了这些能量
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.73,0:36:19.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时 沃尔夫冈·泡利感叹
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.53,0:36:22.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如此微小的虚幻微粒
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.97,0:36:24.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,迅速而难以琢磨
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.90,0:36:27.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能永远都探测不到了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.97,0:36:31.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好在那只是他罕有的一次错误预测
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.41,0:36:33.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为科学家总是不断
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.61,0:36:35.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,寻找探索的新方法
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.48,0:36:37.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几十年后
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.42,0:36:39.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中微子第一次被人们探测到
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.78,0:36:42.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在核反应堆的辐射中
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.39,0:36:46.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然很艰难 但从那之后我们不断找到更多的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.32,0:36:49.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如今 有些科学家们
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.23,0:36:52.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尝试利用那些中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.50,0:36:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来研究时间的起源
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.50,0:37:03.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一起去看看他们的成就  那是一面永恒之墙
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.40,0:37:13.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,永恒之墙并不新鲜
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.17,0:37:15.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的祖先也遇到过
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.14,0:37:18.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几乎就在他们第一次开始想象时
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.28,0:37:23.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几千年前 公元前13世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.08,0:37:26.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,埃及人建造了阿布辛贝勒神庙
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.62,0:37:28.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,纪念法老王拉美西斯二世
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.69,0:37:31.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这里留下了四座巨大的石像
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.92,0:37:37.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这位伟大君主之上真正的王者其实是鹰首太阳神
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:40.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳之神
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.54,0:37:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这座神庙被设计成每年只有两次
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.44,0:37:52.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,旭日的霞光金辉才会射入神殿
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.78,0:37:55.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当光线照进神庙
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.81,0:37:59.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在贯穿整个神殿前
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.45,0:38:03.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,日光使众神的石像闪耀着金色的光芒
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.45,0:38:07.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是 仍有一位神的石像依然处在阴影中
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.46,0:38:09.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,普塔 创造之神
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.96,0:38:15.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仿佛暗示宇宙的起源注定永远神秘
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.74,0:38:21.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,感受阳光照在脸上
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.57,0:38:24.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使你温暖的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.17,0:38:27.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来自几千万年前
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.34,0:38:29.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳的核心
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.48,0:38:32.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与中微子不同
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.55,0:38:34.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,质子需要
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.38,0:38:37.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这么久的时间才能从核心到达表面
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.39,0:38:39.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为啥
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.42,0:38:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们与太阳的原子每秒发生几十亿次的碰撞
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.76,0:38:47.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每次撞击都将它们推向不同的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.66,0:38:49.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们一旦到达表面
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.66,0:38:52.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们就彻底解放 以光的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.84,0:38:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只用区区8分20秒 就来到你的面前
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.57,0:39:02.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一千万岁高龄的阳光
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.08,0:39:10.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当那光离开太阳核心时 又是怎么的景象呢
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.62,0:39:18.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙年历将宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.69,0:39:21.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整整138亿年的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.53,0:39:23.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,压缩到一年的时间内
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.63,0:39:27.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个月代表10亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.20,0:39:30.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一天就是4千万年
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.10,0:39:33.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙的历史如此悠久 在年历上
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.37,0:39:37.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1千万年前 也只不过是
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.14,0:39:43.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一年的最后一天的下午6点
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.65,0:39:45.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那我们呢
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.25,0:39:47.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类还没开始进化
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.12,0:39:48.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1千万年前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.89,0:39:51.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的祖先还是类人猿
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.32,0:39:53.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,活跃在非洲的丛林中
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.26,0:39:56.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对我们来说 1千万年好像很久远
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.76,0:39:59.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是对于宇宙来说
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.17,0:40:01.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那只不过是半天而已
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.97,0:40:09.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,45亿年前 太阳开始放出光芒
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.94,0:40:13.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙历上的8月31号
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.68,0:40:15.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的银河系
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.75,0:40:18.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约100亿岁
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.85,0:40:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一个星系比它还早几十亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.96,0:40:27.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有东西阻挡我们回到更远的过去
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.93,0:40:29.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是什么呢
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.60,0:40:35.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是光与时间的本质
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.50,0:40:38.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为光的速度有限
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.70,0:40:43.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看向宇宙其实看到的是过去的光
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:48.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看的越远
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.78,0:40:51.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到的光越古老
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.62,0:40:56.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是我们所能看到宇宙历史上最古老的光
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.45,0:40:58.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是宇宙刚诞生的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.89,0:41:01.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有38万岁
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.99,0:41:07.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙历上最初的15分钟
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.66,0:41:12.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们用微波望远镜看向宇宙的尽头
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.84,0:41:14.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到的就是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.30,0:41:17.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大爆炸留下的光晕
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.64,0:41:21.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想象一下 可观测宇宙的所有物质和能量
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.54,0:41:25.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都被浓缩成这样的大小
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.85,0:41:29.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是当时宇宙的大小
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.75,0:41:35.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当它只有1.0e-36秒时
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.16,0:41:38.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几千亿个星系的物质与能量
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.73,0:41:41.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如今扩展到方圆几十亿光年的范围
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.83,0:41:46.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,曾经都被禁锢在这个弹珠大小的东西内
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.20,0:41:50.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你能想象出那颗弹珠有多紧密吗
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.17,0:41:53.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,稠密得使任何光都无法穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.04,0:41:56.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这阻碍不了中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.84,0:41:59.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大爆炸必定产生了数量惊人的中微子
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.75,0:42:03.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们顺畅地穿过那些紧密得难以置信的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.45,0:42:06.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使它们几乎无法被探测的最关键因素是
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.69,0:42:13.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们可以穿过遮掩时间起源的厚重幕布
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.46,0:42:15.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们在哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.06,0:42:16.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这里 在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.63,0:42:18.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙中无处不在
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.87,0:42:21.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙诞生时中微子就在你的内心深处
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.77,0:42:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从一个弹珠
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:27.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到整个宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:43.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一条泰利斯和德谟克利特2500年前带我们走上的路
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.92,0:42:45.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无尽的探索之路
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.99,0:42:49.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不断地有条不紊地探索新的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.33,0:42:51.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且不断加深对自然的理解
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.43,0:43:00.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你们中有人会接过火炬 带领我们走上一条更宽广的大路吗
